{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When a task involves multiple operations that must happen in a specific order, a step-by-step prompt structure prevents the model from collapsing the sequence into a single ambiguous instruction. Autoregressive models generate left-to-right without backtracking — if a model jumps to the final answer without performing intermediate steps, there is no mechanism to correct the reasoning mid-flight. Numbered step instructions force the model to treat each stage as an independent sub-task and make its working visible, both of which improve accuracy on multi-stage problems."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Step-by-Step — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Sequential Structure Helps"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single instruction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Numbered steps"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step ordering"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model decides; may reorder"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enforced by prompt structure"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Intermediate results"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hidden in one-shot answer"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Visible; each step anchors the next"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Error diagnosis"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hard — wrong answer, no trail"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Easy — find the first wrong step"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Accuracy on multi-hop tasks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lower — model shortcuts"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Higher — working is verified at each stage"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-Step Prompt Patterns"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n\ndef ask(prompt: str, max_tokens: int = 300) -> str:\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=max_tokens,\n        temperature=0.0,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n\n\nCODE = \"\"\"\ndef calculate_discount(price, discount_pct):\n    discount = price * discount_pct\n    final = price + discount          # bug: should subtract\n    return round(final, 2)\n\"\"\"\n\n# Single instruction — model may skip steps or merge them\nprint(\"--- Single instruction ---\")\nprint(ask(f\"Fix the bug and add a docstring:\\n{CODE}\"))\nprint()\n\n# Numbered steps — each operation is explicit and ordered\nprint(\"--- Numbered steps ---\")\nprint(ask(f\"\"\"Perform these steps on the code below:\n1. Identify the bug and state it in one sentence.\n2. Fix the bug.\n3. Add a one-line docstring that describes the function.\n4. Return only the corrected code with docstring.\n\nCode:\n{CODE}\"\"\"))\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chaining Steps Across API Calls"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n\ndef call(prompt: str, max_tokens: int = 150) -> str:\n    resp = client.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\n        max_tokens=max_tokens,\n        temperature=0.0,\n        messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}],\n    )\n    return resp.content[0].text.strip()\n\n\nARTICLE = \"\"\"Scientists at MIT have developed a new battery chemistry using\nsodium ions instead of lithium. The prototype stores 40% more energy per\nkilogram than current lithium-ion cells and uses materials costing one-fifth\nas much. The team expects commercial production within five years.\"\"\"\n\n# Step 1: extract key claims\nclaims_raw = call(\n    f\"List the factual claims in this article, one per line, no preamble:\\n\\n{ARTICLE}\"\n)\nprint(\"Claims:\\n\", claims_raw)\n\n# Step 2: assess each claim's verifiability\nverifiability = call(\n    f\"For each claim below, label it VERIFIABLE or SPECULATIVE. \"\n    f\"One line per claim: '<claim> → <label>'\\n\\n{claims_raw}\"\n)\nprint(\"\\nVerifiability:\\n\", verifiability)\n\n# Step 3: write a cautious summary using only verifiable claims\nsummary = call(\n    f\"\"\"Write a two-sentence summary of the article.\nOnly include claims labelled VERIFIABLE below. Do not include speculative claims.\n\nVerified claims:\n{verifiability}\n\nSummary:\"\"\"\n)\nprint(\"\\nCautious summary:\\n\", summary)\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to Use In-Prompt Steps vs Multi-Call Chains"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Approach"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Numbered steps in one prompt"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short pipelines where steps share context"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "All steps compete for the same context window"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequential API calls"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Long pipelines; intermediate validation needed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "More latency; must manage state in code"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chain-of-thought elicitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Reasoning tasks where intermediate tokens improve accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Uses more output tokens; reasoning still error-prone"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step-by-step prompting is a forcing function: it prevents the model from treating a multi-stage pipeline as a single pattern-match and instead requires it to generate each stage's output explicitly. The generated intermediate text functions as a scratchpad — each completed step becomes additional context that narrows the space of plausible next steps. For complex tasks, this is more reliable than asking for the answer directly, because the intermediate steps carry information that would otherwise have to live in the model's implicit computation."}]}]}]}}